(115, 1, '2014-08-10 17:55:02', '2014-08-10 11:55:02', '<h1 style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">Difference between JavaScript, Jquery and Ajax</h1>\r\n        <div class="para">\r\n                <b style="color: #ff6600;">JavaScript : </b>Javascript is a client side scripting language provided by the browser so that we can do a level of programming on client side. client side scripting means that the browser will execute the script into.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="para">\r\n                <b style="color: #ff6600;">jQuery : </b>jQuery is the most popular javascript framework. Why use it? Different browser has different idea about how javascript is implemented. jQuery takes a care of this difference and provided us with a unified and very easy way to do coding in javascript.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="para">\r\n                <b style="color: #ff6600;">AJAX(Asynchronous Javascript and XML) : </b>AJAX is a mechanism to fetch data from server without doing a full page load. We need to use javascript to make a ajax call, and we need it again when data is returned from server. AJAX is a mechanism, not a language javascript or framework like jQuery.\r\n        </div>\r\n        <h1 style="font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center;">What is DOM ?</h1>\r\n        <div class="para">\r\n            <b style="color: #ff6600;">DOM(Document Object Model) : </b>When a webpage is parsed by the browser, it creates an in-memory representation of the page. It is a tree structure, which contains all elements on the page. So there is a root element, which contains the head and the body elements, which contain other elements. So it looks like a tree basically. Now with javascript we can manipulate elements in the page using this tree. We can pick elements by their id (getElementsById), or their tag name (getElementsByTagName), or by simply going through the tree (parentNode, firstChild, lastChild, nextSibling, previousSibling, etc.). Once we have element(s) to work with we can modify them by changing their look, content or position on the page. This interface is also known as the DOM.\r\n        </div>\r\n<!--JavaScript Learning Resource-->\r\n<p id="resource">JavaScript Resources</p>\r\n<div style="height: 10px;"></div>\r\n<div class="ol-li-container">\r\n    <ol class="rectangle-list">\r\n       <li><a href="http://www.learn-javascript-tutorial.com/" target="_blank">Javascript Tutorial(It is very important to learn javascript at the beginning)</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://mahtonu.wordpress.com/2010/09/08/good-javascript-study-resources/" target="_blank">Good JavaScript Study Resources[M.A Hossain Tonu blog]</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://bonsaiden.github.com/JavaScript-Garden/" target="_blank">JavaScript Garden</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://net.tutsplus.com/tutorials/javascript-ajax/24-javascript-best-practices-for-beginners/" target="_blank">JavaScript Best Practices</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://www.fiendish.demon.co.uk/html/javascript/layerfloat.html" target="_blank">JavaScript Floating Text</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://www.w3programmers.com/powerful-javascript-form-validation-plugins/" target="_blank">Powerful JavaScript Form Validation Plugins</a></li>			\r\n    </ol>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!--jQuery Learning Resource-->\r\n<div class="clear"></div>\r\n<p id="resource">jQuery Resources</p>\r\n<div style="height: 10px;"></div>\r\n<div class="ol-li-container">\r\n    <ol class="rectangle-list">\r\n       <li><a href="http://tutorialbd.com/jquery/" target="_blank">jQuery বাংলা টিউটোরিয়াল। লেখকঃ আরিফুর রহমান \r\n               (সজল)।</a></li>\r\n       <li><a href="http://api.jquery.com/" target="_blank">jQuery official site</a></li>\r\n       <li><a>jQuery Tester</a></li>\r\n        <ol>\r\n            <li><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/WxrLn/" target="_blank">Tester-1</a></li>\r\n            <li><a href="http://jsbin.com/agorog/5/edit#javascript,html" target="_blank"